{
  "_comment": "RES-2 follow-up — AUDIT profile for the docgrok-pipeline-worker. Identical allow-list to docgrok-parser.json plus defaultAction=SCMP_ACT_LOG so that any syscall NOT in the list is logged to the kernel audit subsystem (auditd / journald) instead of being denied. Operators run this profile in pre-prod for one full ingestion cycle, harvest the syscall list via 'ausearch -k seccomp | grep SECCOMP', diff against docgrok-parser.json, and then promote the audit findings into a tightened production profile.",
  "_origin": "Built from docgrok-parser.json. The only delta is defaultAction.",
  "_usage": "kubectl annotate or helm value security.seccompProfile.localhostProfile=docgrok-parser-audit.json. Do NOT run in production for more than the audit window — SCMP_ACT_LOG is permissive (allows AND logs).",
  "defaultAction": "SCMP_ACT_LOG",
  "architectures": ["SCMP_ARCH_X86_64", "SCMP_ARCH_X86", "SCMP_ARCH_X32"],
